the GameWindow's `OnMaximized` handler is used, the `MaximizedEventArgs` property `IsMaximized` doesn't match the windows `ClientSize` property:\r\n * if `e.IsMaximized == true`, the non-maximized size is reported\r\n * if `e.IsMaximized == false`, the maximized size is reported\r\n\r\n### Repro steps\r\n1 . GL window code:\r\n```c#\r\npublic class Window : GameWindow\r\n{\r\n    public Window()\r\n        : base(GameWindowSettings.Default, NativeWindowSettings.Default)\r\n    {\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    public Window(int width, int heigth, string title)\r\n        : base(GameWindowSettings.Default, new NativeWindowSettings()\r\n        {\r\n            Size = new Vector2i(width, heigth),\r\n            Title = title\r\n        })\r\n    {\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    protected override void OnLoad()\r\n    {\r\n        MakeCurrent();\r\n\r\n        GL.ClearColor(1.0f, 1.0f, 1.0f, 1.0f);\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    protected override void OnMaximized(MaximizedEventArgs e)\r\n    {\r\n        System.Diagnostics.Debug.WriteLine($\"e.IsMaximized: {e.IsMaximized}, ClientSize: {ClientSize}\");\r\n\r\n        base.OnMaximized(e);\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n2 . GL window creation:\r\n```c#\r\nusing (var window = new Window(800, 600, \"OpenTK\"))\r\n{\r\n    GL.LoadBindings(new GLFWBindingsContext());\r\n\r\n    window.IsEventDriven = true;\r\n    window.Run();\r\n}\r\n```\r\n3. Maximize the window, then restore and look at the debug output.\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\nThe debug output should read:\r\n```\r\ne.IsMaximized: True, ClientSize: (1920; 1017)\r\ne.IsMaximized: False, ClientSize: (800; 600)\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Actual behavior\r\nThe debug out reads:\r\n```\r\ne.IsMaximized: True, ClientSize: (800; 600)\r\ne.IsMaximized: False, ClientSize: (1920; 1017)\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Related information \r\n\r\n* Windows 10 x64\r\n* Native backend\r\n* OpenTK 4.4.0 nuget package\r\n* net 5.0\r\n\r\n","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/opentk/opentk/issues/1235/reactions","total_count":0,"